content.statement:
Draw a picture of the open ball 𝖡((0, 0); 1) in the metric space (ℝ2 , d) with
(a) d(𝑥, 𝑦) = d1 (𝑥, 𝑦) = |𝑥1 − 𝑦1 | + |𝑥2 − 𝑦2 |;
√
(b) d(𝑥, 𝑦) = d2 (𝑥, 𝑦) = (𝑥1 − 𝑦1 )2 + (𝑥2 − 𝑦2 )2 ;
(c) d(𝑥, 𝑦) = d∞ (𝑥, 𝑦) = max{|𝑥1 − 𝑦1 |, |𝑥2 − 𝑦2 |}.

Let X be a non-empty set, and let 𝑥0 be an element of X. Show that
 = {𝑈 ⊆ X ∣ 𝑥0 ∉ 𝑈 or X ⧵ 𝑈 is finite}
is a topology on X.

Let X = {a, b, c, d, 𝑒}, and let
 = {∅, {a, b}, {a, b, c}, {a, b, d, 𝑒}, {b}, {b, c}, {b, d, 𝑒}, {b, c, d, 𝑒}, {d, 𝑒}, X}
be a topology on X. Is the subset {a, b} dense in X?

Show that
 = {(a, ∞) ∣ a ∈ ℝ} ∪ {(−∞, b) ∣ b ∈ ℝ}
is a subbasis for the standard topology on ℝ.
